Every activity must be present in the `AndroidManifest.xml` file, and it automatically gets added whenever you create new Activity.
To start your app with different activity than it usually does, you just need to simply place

    &lt;intent-filter&gt;
                    &lt;action android:name=&quot;android.intent.action.MAIN&quot; /&gt;
                    &lt;category android:name=&quot;android.intent.category.LAUNCHER&quot; /&gt;
                &lt;/intent-filter&gt;

in the tags of the activity from which you want your app to start.
And if you want to change the activity name do so by right clicking on the activity in the projects tab then go to refractor then rename.
